CELEBRITY couple Stephanie “Miss Sandows” Ndlovu (31) and Hungani Ndlovu (27) are ready to welcome their first bundle of joy. The couple, who are both actors, shared they’re pregnant on their Instagram accounts on Sunday, 17 July. Stephanie shared photos of them together, finally revealing their pregnancy. Just a few months ago, the actress shared how they lost their previous baby to a miscarriage on their YouTube channel. Hungani also shared their pregnancy photos on his Instagram. Stephanie wrote: “And when the time is right, I, The Lord, will make it happen.” While her husband praised God for the amazing gift they are about to receive. “God is the ultimate author #thendlovusarepregnant,” he wrote. ALSO READ: Repo man guns for soccer star's BMW! The pair got married in 2019. They have been together for the past six years and are still going strong. The couple have a YouTube channel called The Ndlovu Uncut. This is where they talk about their love life and marriage. Messages from their fans flooded their comments sections with words of encouragements and hope. Actress Zola Nombona wrote: “Congratulations my loves.” “This right here is everything and more of God’s blessings. Congratulations mama,” Khutso Theledi wrote. Kagiso Nokwena said Stephanie gave her hope as she once lost her baby through a miscarriage. “You have restored my faith and hope because I was already giving up,” she said. Actress Pasi Koetle congratulated the couple on their pregnancy. A post shared by HUNGANI NDLOVU ?? DJ GRIZI?? (@hunganindlovu)  